  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" State of Punjab & Ors. versus Trishala Alloys Pvt. Ltd. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_2_1948_1968','2025INSC231'); ><font size='4'> <strong>STATE OF PUNJAB & ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>TRISHALA ALLOYS PVT. LTD. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 2 S.C.R. 1948</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 231</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007172025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the State could amend the Punjab Value Added Tax Rules, 2005 to provide that the input tax credit (ITC) already earned on goods kept in stock could be availed at a reduced rate as the rate of tax on the goods stood reduced in the interregnum when there was no statute i.e., the Punjab Value Added Tax Act, 2005. Headnotes&dagger; Punjab Value Added Tax Act, 2005 (&ldquo;Punjab VAT Act&rdquo;) &ndash; First proviso to s.13(1) &ndash; Amended with effect from 01.04.2014 &ndash; Punjab Value Added Tax Rules, 2005 (&ldquo;Punjab VAT Rules&rdquo;) &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 17-02-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 2212/2024</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_2_1948_1968','2025INSC231','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-aut